article.headline: Georgia 95, Florida A&M 74
article.story: ATHENS, Ga. (AP) -- Levi Stukes scored 20 points despite an ailing back, Mike Mercer keyed a 19-2 run at the end of the first half and Georgia coasted in its home opener to a 95-74 victory over Florida A&M on Tuesday night. The Bulldogs (4-1) are halfway to their win total for all of last season, when they struggled to an 8-20 mark with only seven scholarship players and a starting lineup composed solely of sophomores and freshmen. Georgia is still rebuilding from the Jim Harrick-era scandals but has clearly improved its talent level with freshmen such as Mercer and Billy Humphrey. Mercer scored eight straight points to help the Bulldogs pull away. He banked one off the glass, drove to the hoop for another basket, knocked down a 3-pointer and made a free throw to push the Georgia lead to 44-29. The Bulldogs kept it up the rest of the half, going to the locker room with a commanding 55-30 advantage over the Rattlers (2-2). Mercer scored 13 of his 16 points before the break. Humphrey also did his best work in the first half. He scored 15 points in the opening half, hitting three shots from beyond the arc, going 4-of-4 at the foul line, grabbing four rebounds and doling out four assists. The freshman wound up with 18 points. Channing Toney added 16 and Sundiata Gaines 12 for the Bulldogs, who shot nearly 59 percent in the first half and finished 32-of-63 from the field. Stukes played only 10 minutes in each half. During his down time, he stretched out on the floor in front of the bench, trying to ease the pain in his back. But Stukes looked just fine in the second half, hitting 5-of-6 from 3-point range. Lamar Twitty led Florida A&M with 13 points, and Rome Sanders was the only other player in double figures with 11. The Rattlers shot just 37 percent, their woes summed up in the opening minute of the second half when Brian Greene missed a layup, then shot an airball on a free throw. It was the third highest-scoring game of Georgia coach Dennis Felton's three-year tenure. The Bulldogs scored 99 against Florida Atlantic in his first season, and defeated Savannah State 100-60 last year.
